{{Hedonism}} '''Esperanza Guisán''' (23 April 1940 – 27 November 2015) was a Spanish [[Moral philosophy|moral]] and [[Political philosophy|political]] [[Philosophy|philosopher]]. She was a professor at the [[University of Santiago de Compostela]]. Her work was devoted mainly to classical [[Utilitarianism|utilitarian]] theory.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lavozdegalicia.es/santiago/2010/09/21/0003_8737356.htm|title=Esperanza Guisán recibirá un homenaje en el curso "Razón e paixóns no utilitarismo"|date=20 September 2010|work=[[La Voz de Galicia]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=29 June 2011}}</ref> A list of many of her works appears at her Google Scholar Web page, including treatises on ethics, democracy, ethics without religion, and Kant.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://scholar.google.es/scholar?star=0&q=Esperanza+Guisan&hl=es&as_sdt=0,5|title=Esperanza Guisan - Google Académico|work=google.es}}</ref><ref>http://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/galicia/2015/11/28/fallece-esperanza-guisan-seijas-catedratica-emerita-etica-usc/0003_201511G28P8992.htm</ref>
